By comparing the communication complexity \(T\) required to achieve a \(\epsilon\)-stationary solution, we can see that our result recovers that of SCAFFOLD when \(N=1\) and \(E=1\). Specifically, for our MTGC algorithm, to achieve an \(\epsilon\) error bound, according to Corollary 4.1, we can find a \(T\) to satisfy

